SUBJECT- AUTO COST INDEXES

WHEN PLANNING A COST INDEX, 2 OPTIONS ARE AVAILABLE. PILOTS
MAY EITHER SELECT A SPECIFIC COST INDEX NUMBER FROM THE
LIST, OR THEY MAY SELECT "AUTO". WHEN PLANNING AN "AUTO"
COST INDEX, THE SYSTEM WILL REFERENCE THE SCHEDULED "TIME
ENROUTE" OPTION AND ATTEMPT TO CHOOSE A COST INDEX WHICH
CLOSELY MATCHES THIS VALUE. NOTE THAT THE "TIME ENROUTE"
OPTION IS MEANT AS A GATE TO GATE TIME (AS INDICATED ON AN
AIRLINE'S FLIGHT SCHEDULE, FOR EXAMPLE). IF A "TIME ENROUTE"
OF 2:30 IS SELECTED, THE SYSTEM WILL SUBTRACT THE TAXI TIMES
FROM THIS VALUE TO DETERMINE THE SCHEDULED AIR TIME. IT WILL
THEN DETERMINE AND USE THE COST INDEX WHICH MATCHES THIS AIR
TIME.
